reviews.text:
Really good recipe.  I ended up using FA Nut Mix instead of Hazel Grove because the Hazelnut I've got is FW, and I wanted to use the same percentages.  Worked out nicely (Edit: since writing this review, I have tried this recipe exactly as written and it is equally delicious).  I'm thinking Almond would also be nice &amp; play well with the Torrone.  If I make this again, I will probably increase the Cuban Supreme to 2.5%.  Thanks! &#xD;
&#xD;
Update:  I actually went back and added another 1.0% Cuban Supreme to this mix, for a total of 3.0%, and I like it much more.   This is a great recipe, for anyone wanting to taste more of the tobacco I would recommend upping the Cuban and perhaps dropping the Torrone to .75% or even .5%.

Rich, creamy -- citrus from Catalan Cream gets lost, vanilla holds, maybe the Torrone adds to the cream. The nut is prominent -- excellent after dinner vape!!&#xD;
&#xD;
You can't go wrong with Cuban Supreme :&gt;
